<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="chp1sec1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>What are integers</title>

  <p> Text of section. </p>


  <question>
		<title>What are integers?</title>
		<p>
			We work with integers every day - but what are they?!  Give your definition of integers.
		</p>
	</question>


  <definition xml:id="def-definition-commutative-ring">
    <title>Commutative Ring with Identity</title>
    <statement>
        <p>
            A <term>commutative ring with identity</term> is a set <m>R</m> with two binary operations: 
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  an addition operation <m>+</m> and a
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                 <p>
                  multiplication operation <m>\cdot</m>
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
            satisfying 6 axioms:
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  (Addition is <term>associative</term>.) If <m>a,b,c \in R</m>, then <m>(a+b)+c=a+(b+c)</m>
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  (Addition has an <term>identity</term>.) If <m>a \in R</m>, then <m>(a+b)+c=a+(b+c)</m>
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  (Addition has <term>inverses</term>.) If <m>a \in R</m>, then there exists <m>-a \in R</m> so that <m>a+(-a)0</m>
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  (Addition is <term>commutative</term>.) If <m>a,b,c \in R</m>, then <m>a+b=(b+a)</m>
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  (Multiplication is <term>associative</term>.) If <m>a,b,c \in R</m>, then <m>(ab)c=a(bc)</m>
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  (Multiplication has an <term>identity</term>.) If <m>a \in R</m>, then <m>1a=a</m>
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>




</section>